# Backend Integration & Database Module

## Overview

This module is responsible for the backend integration of the AI Resume & Placement Assistant project.

It provides:

- User Authentication
- Resume Management
- Dashboard APIs
- MongoDB Database Integration
- Backend API Integration
- Communication with AI Engine and Resume Analysis modules

---

## Features

### User Authentication

- User Registration
- User Login
- JWT Authentication
- Password Hashing
- Protected Routes

---

### Resume Management

- Upload Resume
- View Uploaded Resumes
- Delete Resume
- Store Resume Metadata

---

### Dashboard

Provides APIs to retrieve user information including:

- User Profile
- Uploaded Resume Details
- Resume Count
- Dashboard Summary

---

### Database

MongoDB is used as the primary database.

Collections include:

- users
- resumes

---

## Tech Stack

- FastAPI
- MongoDB Atlas
- Motor (Async MongoDB Driver)
- Pydantic
- JWT Authentication
- Python

---

## Project Structure

backend/
```

auth.py
resume.py
dashboard.py
config.py
interview.py

```

database/
```

user_schema.py
resume_schema.py
interview_schema.py

```

---

## API Endpoints

### Authentication

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|---------|----------|-------------|
| POST | /signup | Register User |
| POST | /login | Login User |

---

### Resume

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|---------|----------|-------------|
| POST | /upload-resume | Upload Resume |
| GET | /resumes | Get User Resumes |
| DELETE | /resume/{id} | Delete Resume |

---

### Dashboard

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|---------|----------|-------------|
| GET | /dashboard | Dashboard Data |

---

## Installation

Clone the repository

```bash
git clone <repository-url>
```

Create virtual environment

```bash
python -m venv venv
```

Activate virtual environment

### macOS/Linux

```bash
source venv/bin/activate
```

### Windows

```bash
venv\Scripts\activate
```

Install dependencies

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

---

## Environment Variables

Create a `.env` file:

```

MONGO_URI=your\_mongodb\_connection
GEMINI\_API\_KEY=your\_gemini\_key
JWT\_SECRET=your\_secret

```

---

## Running the Backend

```bash
uvicorn backend.interview:app --reload
```

Server will run at:

```

http://127.0.0.1:8000

```

Swagger Documentation:

```

http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs

```

